---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '../site.config';
import Link from '../components/ui/Link.astro';
---

<Layout title={`Privacy Policy | ${SITE_CONFIG.brand.name}`} description={`Our commitment to your privacy and data ownership in the ${SITE_CONFIG.brand.name} ecosystem.`}>
  <div class="pt-32 pb-24 md:pt-48 md:pb-40 bg-midnight relative overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Visual Decorations -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/4 w-[600px] h-[600px] bg-white/[0.02] blur-[150px] rounded-full pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <nav class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-text-dim mb-12">
            <Link href="/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</Link>
            <span class="opacity-20">/</span>
            <span class="text-white">Privacy</span>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black text-text-main mb-12 tracking-tighter uppercase leading-tight">
            Privacy <br/> Protocol<span class="text-white opacity-20">.</span>
        </h1>

        <div class="prose prose-zinc prose-invert max-w-none 
            prose-p:text-text-muted prose-p:font-light prose-p:leading-relaxed 
            prose-headings:text-text-main prose-headings:font-black prose-headings:uppercase prose-headings:tracking-tight
            prose-strong:text-white prose-strong:font-bold">
            
            <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl !leading-relaxed mb-16 border-l-2 border-white/10 pl-8 italic">
                {SITE_CONFIG.brand.name} is built on the foundation of transparency and data sovereignty. We believe your technical knowledge belongs to you, and your privacy is non-negotiable.
            </p>

            <h2>1. Zero Data Collection</h2>
            <p>
                By default, the core {SITE_CONFIG.brand.name} engine does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. As a static site generator, all processing happens during build-time or locally within your browser. We do not use tracking cookies, finger-printing, or hidden analytics.
            </p>

            <h2>2. Data Ownership</h2>
            <p>
                All documentation content, metadata, and configuration files reside within your own repository. {SITE_CONFIG.brand.name} has no "cloud" component that stores your data. You have complete control over where your documentation is hosted and who has access to it.
            </p>

            <h2>3. Local Persistence</h2>
            <p>
                To improve your user experience, we use <strong>localStorage</strong> to remember UI preferences, such as:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Sidebar collapsible group states (open/closed).</li>
                <li>Theme preferences (if applicable).</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                This data never leaves your device and is not accessible by us or any third party.
            </p>

            <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>
                {SITE_CONFIG.brand.name} is designed to be self-contained. However, depending on your configuration, you may choose to integrate third-party services:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>GitHub:</strong> Used for fetching contributor avatars and hosting the repository.</li>
                <li><strong>Hosting Providers:</strong> If you deploy to Vercel, Netlify, or similar platforms, they may collect standard web server logs (IP addresses, user agents) as part of their infrastructure.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>5. Open Source Audit</h2>
            <p>
                Our codebase is 100% open-source. We encourage security researchers and users to audit our source code on GitHub to verify our privacy claims.
            </p>

            <div class="mt-24 pt-12 border-t border-white/5">
                <p class="text-xs text-text-dim uppercase tracking-widest font-black">
                    Last Protocol Update: February 5, 2026
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>